&quot;If I can't roll on nice items theres no reason for me to come, I mean I can just get on my a_lvl_60_Monk and go to CoV to get better loot.  Sorry.&quot;<br>
Which is kinda discouraging to me.  Test server shoulden't be that way!  Should it?  I mean how much Druid loot do you think Naggy dropped (besides useless Heirophants crook which I got on my first raid) for me?  I'm going to make a seperate thread so I can get some real feedback on this.  I'll take a vote on a couple of options and abide by whatever the mob says, but possibly not for this Naggy raid depending on how many people respond right away.  Oops!  Patch's done, I'll post that thread later when I've drawn up some feasable options.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  EDIT: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm14.showMessage?topicID=409.topic">Heres the link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uwarpathorcface.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarpathOrcface</A> at: 3/19/02 5:21:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#292929><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ucrouchinglizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crouching Lizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/19/02 3:44:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jumpspot.net/eq/crouchinglizard-rotlc.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot Rules Amendments</span><hr size=1> Well, the 'if you are 55, you can kill a bigger dragon' concept sounds good, except that there are precious few open dragon raids for the big guys.  They are mostly killed by large guilds that don't need outside help.  So if you are independant or in a smaller guild, you will not have many chances at them.<br>
<br>
But with Naggy &amp; Vox, due to the level restriction, even the big guilds have to open up the raids and it has the side effect of providing some folks a decent chance at some nice items they might not have a chance at otherwise.  But of course they can't stay 52 forever, which is where the alts come in.  A person can help in a dragon raid with an alt 50 cleric, or whatnot, and therefore earn a chance at nice haste for his 55 warrior, for example.<br>
<br>
And don't get me wrong -- I'm not mad or anything.  And every raid leader has the right to set whatever rules they wish as long as people are aware of them beforehand.  But this is just where I, and possibly some other folks, are coming from.  Laters,<br>
<br>
