          My two cents .. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#292929><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uh0110w.showPublicProfile?language=EN>h0110w</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/h0110w_3q/Watching.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/19/02 11:41:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/h0110w_3q/Phirean.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot rules, to be or not to be?</span><hr size=1> I don't want to kick a dead horse, nor start and argument, but I'm constantly amazed that people don't like doing raids just for the hell of it. Not that I'm trying to change anybody's opinion, I see a lot of posts that both agree or disagree, and that's fine. Warpath: you don't really need to worry about changing your rules to get more people to come. Provided you post on the registry that you're doing a dragon, well enough in advance, you'll get enough people to come who won't need to roll for a different character, if that's the issue. No, I'm not saying that rolling for an alt is wrong, but if your intent is to get some lower level characters some higher level gear, then by all means do so. I'll be there either way, provided I still have characters in the necessary range, and have the time. Killing a dragon is fun. Meeting new people is fun. Doing both at the same time is, you guessed it, fun. I'm here to play a game, and enjoy my time doing so, and I know quite a few people that are of the same mind.<br>
<br>
So, to make a long story short, I don't think your rules are unfair. Of course, there's going to be people who disagree, but that's life; you can never make everybody happy. If you feel you need to change your loot policy because you can never get enough people to attend, however, then go ahead. Once again, I shouldn't think you'll need to, and don't do it just because you feel pressured to. <p>------------------<br>
Phirean Ycze</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ucrouchinglizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crouching Lizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/20/02 8:21:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jumpspot.net/eq/crouchinglizard-rotlc.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Loot rules, to be or not to be?</span><hr size=1> And I agree, Phirean.  You can't ever please everyone.  And you probably shouldn't change the rules for this raid.  The only thing you might do is listen to the various viewpoints presented and consider them when you do your next raid.  Good luck guys!<br>
<br>
